modules.description: Provides functions to format and output structured data such as boxes, lists, arrays, and tables in both text and HTML formats. Operates on OCaml's native data structures including lists, arrays, and custom box types. Used to generate readable, styled representations of complex data for debugging or documentation purposes.

Places boxes at specified coordinates or along a grid based on a callback function, supporting scatterplots and decision boundaries. Works with coordinate points, box content, and graph configurations, including axis labels and sizing. Renders content_true or content_false at dense grid points, with overlap handled by plot order.
